                <h2 class="animated bounce delay-0s with-eight" style="color:rgb(223, 135, 53)">How To Get It ?</h2>
                <br />
                <h3 class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">To get Kali Linux you have 2 solutions (most commons technics):</h3>
                <br />
                <dt class="animated slideInLeft delay-0s with-eight" style="color:rgb(247, 166, 166)">1.Install Kali Linux on pc :</dt>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -download kali linux's image file </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -create a bootable usb and plug it into a laptop or a pc (when it's off). </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -switch on the computer and go into the bios. </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -then boot on the usb drive (from the boot menu in the bios)to install it ... </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -that's it , you have kali linux on your computer .... </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 0px;color:rgb(150, 250, 125)">   -PS : if you want to run kali linux select "kali linux live" when you booted on the usb key . </p>
                <br />
