                <dt class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="color:rgb(247, 166, 166)">2.Install Kali Linux in a virtual machine :</dt>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -download kali linux's image file </p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -install a software like virtual-box, or vmware .</p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -then add a new VM with the kali linux img file</p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 40px;color:rgb(255, 255, 255)">   -you have your kali linux VM</p>
                <p class="animated slideInRight delay-0s with-eight" style="margin-left: 0px;color:rgb(150, 250, 125)">   -PS : put the mouse pointer on the image to make it appear. </p>
